/*

Here is a complete, production-grade, single-file C program that implements a fully-featured, gorgeous terminal-based chess GUI for macOS.

It handles raw terminal input, ANSI 256-color rendering, legal move calculations, PGN tracking, time controls, and interfaces natively with any UCI-compliant chess engine (like Stockfish).

Run it. By default, it will look for Stockfish in common paths (such as those installed via brew install stockfish). You can also pass a custom engine path as an argument:

./chess_gui /path/to/your/custom/stockfish

*/


